HEADWORD: Shakedown
<hw>Shake"down`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A temporary
substitute for a bed, as one made on the floor or on chairs; -- perhaps
originally from the shaking down of straw for this purpose.</def>
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- shake down, v. t. subject to extortion. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

